r. <br><br>Other than the fact that I raised myself to level 5 in one weekend (not hard to do for someone with past EQ experience)... I started really doing some character development for my necromancer Moandor. Basically, Moandor is an ass. He is discordant evil, selfish and conceited. He is of the &quot;bow down to me you worms&quot; variety. He is a necro by profession, a loner by definition. And he knows he will rarely make friends. But this is really how I want him to role play, as a pompous arrogant jerk. Playing on FV is part of the challenge. Playing an evil character is even more of a challenge. Role playing an evil worm (and sticking with it despite the fact that I will prolly never get a smile or a hug from the likes of sexy wood elf hotties) is the biggest challenge of all. <br><br>I draw the line between gameplay and roleplay. When I'm playing in a group, Moandor's huge ego has to take a back seat to make sure that fellow players are not endangered. And yes, he has even died trying to save the rest of the party.... as in &quot;Everyone run to zone!!! Let the kodiak chase me, I'm already dead, just run!!!&quot; <br><br>But during socializing hour, when there is no combat going on, I play him to the hilt. I just had a great time bickering with a great role playing Ogre, letting him know that he's just a big smelly intruder to Neriak. Of course, he thought that I was just a pompous deluded necromancer loner who will one day come back begging for Ogre friends like him. Hah!!  There was a lot of glaring and snarling and snickering between our characters. What puzzed me is that his tiny pea brain allowed him to speak the superior Teir'Dal language so fluently. Oh well.... <br><br>So far I like it here in FV server. I did notice (as mentioned already) that everyone really is genuinely poor or broke and cash strapped in the server... and finding money is really a struggle, especially for starting characters like mine. Every freakin silver or copper counts. I almost starved to death during level 4, because I bought my spells, but had no coppers left for muffins! I literally had to kill some Nektulos wolves just to get some meat and feed myself. Talk about challenging! LOL <br><br>So if you happen to run into an arrogant sneering elitist DE necromancer named Moandor in the server... don't sweat it. I'm just role playing. Simply sacrifice your first born to me and it's all good. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 9:04:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sarhea looks at this &quot;Moandor&quot;, blandly.  </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  <br><br>&quot;friendly sort, huh? Well, just show some respect to the League and I don't care what else you do.&quot;<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> She shrugs and walks off.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br><br>ooc: Welcome aboard. *smile* <br><br>~Sarhea, halfelven warrior of the Father<br>League of Shadows <p><p align="center"><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner"><b><font color="#710672" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea</font></a><fontface="arial" size="-1"> <br></b><em>A gleaming drop of blood red Hate.</em></font></p><p align="center"><font face="arial" size="-1"><em>Evil, searing, mindless Pain.</em></font></p><p align="center"><font face="arial" size="-1"><em>Blinding,screaming, numbing Rage.©</em></font></p>