ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> I actually feel kind of guilty sometimes in the course of playing my character. He's a terrible incurable racist; anyone who isn't Iksar is a &quot;softskin THING&quot; not worthy of licking the mud off his boots. Our whole guild is actually based on that Iksar-above-all concept. So when a dark elf comes up and /bows and tosses heals at us and asks if he can group with us... well, he gets /snarled at and told to move along before I wash my pike with his blood.<br><br>As a player, I feel bad, 'cause I know how hard it can be to find a group, especially on this server with its low population. But if I compromised my character's IC views for the sake of accomodating other players, it'd make FV that much less of a roleplaying server for me. The best I can do is not actively hunt them down and try to force a confrontation/duel (which is what my character would oftentimes LIKE to do, damn softskins have no business on Kunark <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), on the excuse that, &quot;Well, as long as it's not getting in my way or shooting its mouth off, there's no point in bothering with it. It's beneath my notice.&quot; And if I do challenge to duel and they refuse, it's, &quot;Oh, well, it's a coward, no honor to be had from killing it anyway.&quot;<br><br>So, um, all I can say is, if you run into anyone in our guild and we're less-than-polite to you, it's nothing personal. You just don't have scales. Or you do have scales and you profess to like those who don't. We're not too keen on that, either. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>(Makes a note, I need to learn to speak Teir'Dal just for all the OOC apologies... hehe.)<br><br>Voskor Oth<br>Judicator of Skathris Ven'Sho<br>Fanatic Patriot of Cabilis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 12:24:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> Hail<br><br>I don't know if this thread was actually soliciting advice about how to RP a jerk without annoying people ooc, but I've got at least one piece of advice to give, and one statement to make that hopefully people will take at face value and not get insulted by.<br><br>Statement: Some people (seems like a lot, but that might just be the memories looming large) use RPing evil as an excuse to be assholes.  All kinds of anti-social behaviour ensues.  That doesn't sound like you in the least, the very fact that you are drawing a distincition proves that, but I thought I would point it out.  It is the reason for the following advice.<br><br>Advice: With new people, when you are going to RP, send them a private tell explaining you are RPing.  I know, it really should not be necessary on an RP server, but them are the breaks.  Fortunately, you don't have to do it all the time with your regular friends.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Assuming a twisted little gnomish necro with delusions of adequecy ever makes friends....<br><br>Thanks lots for being one of those people willing to both RP and make concessions to grouping dynamics.  My absolute favorite kind of people!  I find it's pretty common, also.  Tunare bless FV.  If not for this shard, I'd still be a retired EQer.  Though I sure did seem to get a lot more done when I was retired....  Oh well.<br><br>In Service<br><br>Valquiss Silverpalm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 12:38:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> Valquiss brings up an interesting point, and i&quot;m going to give my take on it.<br><br>Rping evil will get those who don't RP all in yer grits about being an ass. And generally, when sent an ooc tell saying look, it's all good, that's just my character, then things are ok.  My own solutions to the ones who still don't get it is very simple   /ignore &lt;randomturd_001&gt;. All in all, make sure you find people who RP to hang out with. You see much much less of that kind of stuff that way. And Rp DOES breed off itself, which I think is a wonderful, fantastic thing. <p><p align="center"><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner"><b><font color="#710672" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea</font></a><fontface="arial" size="-1"> <br></b><em>A gleaming drop of blood red Hate.</em></font></p><p align="center"><font face="arial" size="-1"><em>Evil, searing, mindless Pain.</em></font></p><p align="center"><font face="arial" size="-1"><em>Blinding,screaming, numbing Rage.©